HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 791
By Hakeem
A RESOLUTION to honor the Construction Specifications Institute
for outstanding service to the commercial
construction industry.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing
those dedicated professionals who work to improve communication among stakeholders in their
respective fields; and
WHEREAS, the Construction Specifications Institute (CSI) was founded in 1948 "to
advance building information management and education of project teams to improve facility
performance" within the commercial construction industry; and
WHEREAS, CSI is a national not-for-profit association with a diverse membership of
more than 6,000 allied professionals who are involved in the creation and management of the
built environment; and
WHEREAS, CSI and its members are dedicated to improving the communication of
construction information throughout continuous development and transformation of standards
and formats, education and certification of professionals to improve project delivery processes,
and creation of practice tools to assist users throughout the facility life-cycle; and
WHEREAS, CSI is renowned in the industry for its rigorous certification programs, which
include Construction Documents Technologist, Certified Construction Specifier, Certified
Construction Contract Administrator, and Certified Construction Product Representative; and
WHEREAS, CSI chapters across the country do much more than provide networking
opportunities, they also sponsor high-quality education programs and events that help members
share real-world solutions and better understand the roles and responsibilities of each member
of the construction team; and
HJR0791
011581
- 1 -

WHEREAS, CSI works with organizations around the globe to create and maintain the
standards that guide the construction industry's communication and documentation; and
WHEREAS, CSI is committed to "creating a better world through inclusion" by valuing
individual differences and contributions, promoting dignity and respect for all, and increasing
cultural competency and cultural humility; and
WHEREAS, due to the high quality and great scope of the organization's certification
and education programs, CSI members are well prepared to effectively communicate the
designers' vision, the material producers' solutions, and the constructors' techniques to create
outstanding commercial facilities that meet facility owners' objectives; and
WHEREAS, William Sundquist, FCSI, of Chattanooga currently serves with distinction as
Chairman of the Board of CSI; he has "proudly promoted our shared Tennessee and
Chattanooga values" throughout his journey as the organization's leader; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the leadership and members of the Construction Specifications
Institute for their outstanding service to the commercial construction industry and commend their
ongoing commitment to improving communication among commercial construction
professionals through extensive education, rigorous certification, and uniform standards.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
